Perfect üëç ‚Äî here‚Äôs the **AWS + Java Developer Cheat Sheet (with full service names)**, covering ~20 **major AWS services**, their **Java integration points**, **common use cases**, **key features**, and **caveats** ‚Äî with **fully qualified names** (like ‚ÄúAmazon Simple Storage Service (S3)‚Äù).

---

### ‚òÅÔ∏è **AWS + Java Integration Deep-Dive Cheat Sheet**

| **AWS Service (Full Name)**                         | **Java Integration Points (SDK / Framework)**                      | **Common Use-Cases in Java Applications**                       | **Key Features**                                                | **Caveats / Important Notes**                                  |
| --------------------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------------------ | --------------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2)**              | AWS SDK for Java (`software.amazon.awssdk.services.ec2.Ec2Client`) | Deploy & run Java / Spring Boot apps on virtual machines        | Full OS & JVM control, auto-scaling groups, Elastic IPs         | You manage OS patching, scaling, and JVM tuning manually       |
| **AWS Elastic Beanstalk (EB)**                      | Upload `.jar` / `.war`; AWS EB CLI; AWS SDK                        | Simplified deployment for Java SE / Tomcat applications         | Auto-scaling, load balancing, rolling updates                   | Limited customization vs EC2/ECS; slower provisioning          |
| **AWS Lambda**                                      | `aws-lambda-java-core`, `aws-lambda-java-events` libraries         | Event-driven serverless compute for Java methods                | Auto-scaling, pay-per-use, integrates with S3, SQS, API Gateway | Cold starts higher for Java; use SnapStart or smaller packages |
| **Amazon Elastic Container Service (ECS)**          | AWS SDK (`EcsClient`), Docker image deployment                     | Containerized deployment of Java microservices                  | Managed cluster orchestration, integrates with Fargate          | Set memory limits properly for JVM in containers               |
| **AWS Fargate**                                     | Dockerized Java apps via ECS / EKS                                 | Serverless containers (no EC2 to manage)                        | Scales automatically, secure by design                          | Costs more for long-running workloads                          |
| **Amazon Elastic Kubernetes Service (EKS)**         | Helm / `kubectl` / AWS SDK (`EksClient`)                           | Deploy Java microservices using Kubernetes                      | Managed control plane, integrates with IAM and VPC              | Steeper learning curve, cluster ops overhead                   |
| **Amazon Relational Database Service (RDS)**        | JDBC, Spring Data JPA, AWS Secrets Manager                         | Persistent relational DB for business data                      | Managed backups, Multi-AZ, read replicas                        | Connection limits; use RDS Proxy for Lambda                    |
| **Amazon Aurora (RDS family)**                      | JDBC, Hibernate ORM, Spring Data JPA                               | High-performance relational DB compatible with MySQL/PostgreSQL | Serverless scaling, high availability                           | Version-dependent JDBC driver compatibility                    |
| **Amazon DynamoDB (NoSQL Database)**                | AWS SDK (`DynamoDbClient`), Spring Data DynamoDB                   | Serverless NoSQL store, caching, session data                   | Fully managed, scalable, millisecond latency                    | No joins; requires careful table design                        |
| **Amazon Simple Storage Service (S3)**              | AWS SDK (`S3Client`), Spring Cloud AWS `S3Template`                | Store/upload files, backups, static assets                      | Object storage, versioning, lifecycle policies                  | Eventual consistency for some ops; 5GB PUT limit               |
| **Amazon Simple Queue Service (SQS)**               | AWS SDK (`SqsClient`), Spring Cloud AWS Messaging                  | Message queues for decoupled microservices                      | FIFO & Standard queues, DLQs, visibility timeouts               | Message size ‚â§ 256KB; requires polling                         |
| **Amazon Simple Notification Service (SNS)**        | AWS SDK (`SnsClient`), Spring Cloud AWS                            | Pub/Sub notifications, fan-out messaging                        | Multiple protocols (HTTP, SMS, Lambda)                          | No message persistence; combine with SQS for durability        |
| **Amazon Managed Streaming for Apache Kafka (MSK)** | Apache Kafka Java Client, Spring Kafka                             | Event streaming & log aggregation                               | Fully managed Kafka clusters, IAM auth                          | Cluster config complexity, IAM permissions required            |
| **Amazon ElastiCache (Redis / Memcached)**          | `spring-data-redis`, Jedis/Lettuce clients                         | Caching, distributed sessions, leaderboards                     | In-memory performance, clustering, persistence                  | Eviction & memory planning required                            |
| **Amazon API Gateway**                              | AWS SDK (`ApiGatewayClient`), Spring Boot REST backend             | Expose REST/HTTP APIs for Java microservices                    | Auth integration (Cognito), throttling, caching                 | Payload ‚â§ 10 MB; cold-start if backend = Lambda                |
| **AWS Step Functions**                              | AWS SDK (`SfnClient`), integrate Java Lambdas                      | Orchestrate complex workflows                                   | Visual state machines, retries, error handling                  | Input/output limited (256 KB per step)                         |
| **Amazon CloudWatch**                               | AWS SDK (`CloudWatchClient`), Micrometer integration               | Collect logs, metrics, alarms for Java apps                     | Metrics dashboards, custom alarms, Log Insights                 | Logs stored by region; retention costs                         |
| **AWS X-Ray**                                       | `aws-xray-recorder-sdk-spring`                                     | Distributed tracing in Java microservices                       | Trace AWS SDK calls, latency visualization                      | Slight overhead; enable sampling for cost control              |
| **AWS Secrets Manager**                             | AWS SDK (`SecretsManagerClient`), Spring Cloud AWS                 | Secure credentials & API key storage                            | Encrypted secrets, automatic rotation                           | API latency; cache results in app memory                       |
| **Amazon Cognito**                                  | Spring Security OAuth2 / `AWSCognitoIdentityProviderClient`        | Authentication & SSO for web/mobile apps                        | JWT-based auth, user pools, social sign-in                      | Limited advanced RBAC; customization via triggers              |
| **AWS CodePipeline / CodeBuild / CodeDeploy**       | SDK for automation; Jenkins / GitHub Actions integration           | CI/CD pipeline for building & deploying Java apps               | Automated build, test, deploy, rollback                         | Slower than local CI; YAML config complexity                   |
| **AWS CloudFormation (IaC)**                        | AWS SDK (`CloudFormationClient`), AWS CDK for Java                 | Infrastructure-as-code for app environment                      | Declarative resource templates, drift detection                 | Stack update replaces full resources                           |
| **AWS Cloud Development Kit (CDK)**                 | AWS CDK (Java bindings)                                            | Define AWS resources directly in Java code                      | Strong typing, reuse via constructs                             | Requires build step (`cdk synth`)                              |
| **Amazon CloudFront (CDN)**                         | SDK / console setup with S3 origin                                 | Global content caching for static web apps                      | Edge caching, HTTPS, compression                                | Cache invalidation cost; TTL tuning                            |
| **Amazon Kinesis Data Streams / Firehose**          | AWS SDK (`KinesisClient`), KCL (Java)                              | Real-time log/metric/event streaming                            | Shard-based scalability, integrates with Lambda                 | Throughput limits per shard; partition key design critical     |
| **AWS Glue / Amazon Athena**                        | AWS SDK (`GlueClient`), Athena JDBC driver                         | ETL jobs, ad-hoc querying S3 data                               | Serverless ETL & SQL queries on data lake                       | Pay per query (TB scanned), higher latency                     |
| **AWS Identity and Access Management (IAM)**        | Role-based access via EC2/Lambda; `IamClient`                      | Manage access control for apps & users                          | Fine-grained permissions, role chaining                         | Policy misconfigurations can expose resources                  |

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è **Quick Integration Practices (Java-Focused)**

| **Category**           | **Best Practice / Tool**                                                           |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| **SDK Usage**          | Use **AWS SDK v2 for Java** (async, non-blocking, modular)                         |
| **Spring Integration** | Use **Spring Cloud AWS v3+** (supports Boot 3.x & SDK v2)                          |
| **Credentials**        | Use **IAM Roles** (no hardcoded keys); fallback to `DefaultCredentialsProvider`    |
| **Config Management**  | Store env config in **AWS Systems Manager Parameter Store** or **Secrets Manager** |
| **Logging & Metrics**  | Use **Micrometer + CloudWatch**, **X-Ray** for distributed tracing                 |
| **Deployment**         | Package as **Docker image (Jib / Buildpacks)** and deploy to ECS/Fargate           |
| **Database Layer**     | Use **RDS (JPA)** or **DynamoDB SDK** based on schema flexibility                  |
| **Caching**            | Use **ElastiCache (Redis)** with `spring-data-redis`                               |
| **Messaging**          | Use **SQS/SNS** for simple async, **MSK/Kinesis** for streaming                    |
| **Security**           | Use **Cognito + Spring Security OAuth2** for JWT-based SSO                         |
| **Infrastructure**     | Define via **AWS CDK (Java)** or **CloudFormation YAML/JSON**                      |
| **CI/CD**              | Integrate **CodePipeline + CodeBuild** with GitHub/Jenkins                         |
| **Monitoring**         | Centralize metrics/logs in **CloudWatch**, visualize with **Grafana**              |

---

### üß† **Example AWS Architecture for a Java Application**

| **Layer**      | **AWS Service(s)**                        | **Java Integration / Example**            |
| -------------- | ----------------------------------------- | ----------------------------------------- |
| API Layer      | **Amazon API Gateway / ALB**              | Expose REST APIs for Spring Boot app      |
| Compute        | **ECS (Fargate)** or **Lambda**           | Deploy containerized Java microservice    |
| Data Layer     | **Amazon RDS / DynamoDB**                 | Spring Data JPA or DynamoDB SDK           |
| Messaging      | **Amazon SQS / SNS / MSK**                | Asynchronous event-driven communication   |
| Caching        | **Amazon ElastiCache (Redis)**            | Spring Cache / RedisTemplate              |
| Storage        | **Amazon S3**                             | File uploads & static content             |
| Auth           | **Amazon Cognito**                        | Spring Security OAuth2 integration        |
| Secrets        | **AWS Secrets Manager**                   | Secure DB credentials                     |
| Monitoring     | **Amazon CloudWatch + AWS X-Ray**         | Micrometer metrics + tracing              |
| CI/CD          | **CodePipeline + CodeBuild + CodeDeploy** | Automated build & deployment              |
| Infrastructure | **AWS CloudFormation / CDK (Java)**       | Define all AWS resources programmatically |

